[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Jeremiah 25:8-9",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jeremiah 25:8-9",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Therefore, because ye have not heard ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— That is, because ye have not hearkened to, nor obeyed ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "my words, Behold, I will send and take all the families of the north, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — All those kings whose territories lie northward of Judea, and particularly Nebuchadnezzar, who, in this work, shall be my servant; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and will bring them against this land, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — I will lead, as commander in chief, them and their armies up against this people; and I will deprive you of all hopes of safety from your alliances with other nations, for the king of Babylon shall first subdue them. See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 24:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And will utterly destroy them, and make them an astonishment ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Will make these countries, and their inhabitants, the objects of men’s scorn and reproach. See note on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 24:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And a perpetual desolation",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " — It is often observed, that the Hebrew word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "עולם",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", here rendered ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "perpetual, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "does not always imply eternity, or perpetuity, in a strict sense; but is sometimes taken for such a duration as had a remarkable period to conclude it. Thus it is said of a servant, in a certain case, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 21:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "That he shall serve his master for ever ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Which the Jews interpret as meaning, “till the next jubilee.” So here the sense of the word is to be restrained to the period of seventy years, mentioned ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 25:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
